criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  The inclusion criteria were: being aged between 16 and 70 years;

          -  with a body mass index of 18-25 kg/m2;

          -  with a physical status classified as ASA class I or II;

          -  and scheduled for elective craniotomy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Any patient would be excluded from this study if the patient had complicating serious
             coagulopathy, hepatorenal insufficiency, aortic regurgitation, or cardiac arrhythmia;

          -  had a previous history of intra-aortic balloon counterpulsation;

          -  exhibited systolic blood pressure (SBP) ≥160 mmHg, diastolic blood pressure (DBP) ≥100
             mmHg, or heart rate ≥ 100 bpm on operating room admission;

          -  or rejected to participate in this study.
